<TITLE> ACC sues ex-AIG over illegal assets </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 24 (bdnews24.com)  The Anticorruption Commission Wednesday charged former additional inspector general of police Md Shahidullah Khan with having undeclared assets and concealing information. ACC assistant director Md Toufiqul Islam filed a case with Tejgaon Police Station, also accusing Khan's wife Masuda Khan. Tejgaon Police Station sub-inspector Shafiqul Islam quoting the FIR of the case told bdnews24.com Khan faced charges of having assets worth Tk 75.30 lakh beyond his known income. He showed false donation and loan of Tk 53.30 lakh and concealing property worth Tk 31.28 lakh. His wife has been charged for aiding and abetting him, the FIR added. Khan declared in a wealth statement to the ACC in response to a notice that he possessed Tk 2.45 crore in assets. bdnew
